<TITLE> Tk 150 crore graft in 6 yrs at RHD: ACC </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com)  The Anticorruption Commission has unearthed evidence of corruption ranging around Tk 150 crore in the roads and highways department from 2000 to 2006, said ACC director general Col Hanif Iqbal in a press briefing Thursday. It is believed that government money was embezzled under the pretext of road maintenance in 261 separate projects. The Anticorruption Commission has approved charge-sheets against six persons. The main accused are executive engineer of the education engineering department Harun Ur Rashid along with 2 others, Manikganj municipal chairman Ramjan Ali (accused in 2 cases), former managing director of Jamuna Complex Wahidul Islam, deputy managing director of Prabhati Insurance Nikhil Ranjan and police sergeant Harun-or Rashid. "Officials and contractors embezzled Tk 149.01 crore by manipulating tenders," said the director general and added that an additional Tk 4.71 crore was pilfered through a series of other irregularities. During the state of emergency alone, from 2007 to 2008, the estimated expenditure for 32 projects was Tk 368.37 crore but the approved tender was priced at Tk 305.30 croreleaving Tk 63.07 crore unaccounted, said the ACC official. bdnew
